AI.description: The AI competitors will add logic to this AI so its functions return valid and smart values.

runTurn.description: This is called every time it is this AI.player's turn.

returns.description: Represents if you want to end your turn. True means end your turn, False means to keep your turn going and re-call this function.

currentPlayer.description: The player whose turn it is currently. That player can send commands. Other players cannot.

currentTurn.description: The current turn number, starting at 0 for the first player's turn.

cutSpeed.description: The speed at which Cutters work to do cut Webs.

eggsScalar.description: Constant used to calculate how many eggs BroodMothers get on their owner's turns.

gameObjects.description: A mapping of every game object's ID to the actual game object. Primarily used by the server and client to easily refer to the game objects via ID.

maxTurns.description: The maximum number of turns before the game will automatically end.

movementSpeed.description: The speed at which Spiderlings move on Webs.

players.description: List of all the players in the game.

session.description: A unique identifier for the game instance that is being played.

spitSpeed.description: The speed at which Spitters work to spit new Webs.

weavePower.description: How much web strength is added or removed from Webs when they are weaved.

weaveSpeed.description: The speed at which Weavers work to do strengthens and weakens on Webs.

Game.description: There's an infestation of enemy spiders challenging your queen broodmother spider! Protect her and attack the other broodmother in this turn based, node based, game.
Game.name: Spiders

eggs.description: How many eggs the BroodMother has to spawn Spiderlings this turn.

health.description: How much health this BroodMother has left. When it reaches 0, she dies and her owner loses.

BroodMother.description: The Spider Queen. She alone can spawn Spiderlings for each Player, and if she dies the owner loses.

arguments.description: The Spiderling to consume. It must be on the same Nest as this BroodMother.
arguments.name: spiderling

consume.description: Consumes a Spiderling of the same owner to regain some eggs to spawn more Spiderlings.

returns.description: True if the Spiderling was consumed. False otherwise.

arguments.description: The string name of the Spiderling class you want to Spawn. Must be 'Spitter', 'Weaver', or 'Cutter'.
arguments.name: spiderlingType

spawn.description: Spawns a new Spiderling on the same Nest as this BroodMother, consuming an egg.

returns.description: The newly spwaned Spiderling if successful. Null otherwise.

gameObjectName.description: String representing the top level Class that this game object is an instance of. Used for reflection to create new instances on clients, but exposed for convenience should AIs want this data.

id.description: A unique id for each instance of a GameObject or a sub class. Used for client and server communication. Should never change value after being set.

isDead.description: If this Spider is dead and has been removed from the game.

logs.description: Any strings logged will be stored here. Intended for debugging.

nest.description: The Nest that this Spider is currently on. Null when moving on a Web.

owner.description: The Player that owns this Spider, and can command it.

arguments.description: A string to add to this GameObject's log. Intended for debugging.
arguments.name: message

log.description: Adds a message to this GameObject's logs. Intended for your own debugging purposes, as strings stored here are saved in the gamelog.

cuttingWeb.description: The Web that this Cutter is trying to cut. Null if not cutting.

Cutter.description: A Spiderling that can cut existing Webs.

arguments.description: The web you want to Cut. Must be connected to the Nest this Cutter is currently on.
arguments.name: web

cut.description: Cuts a web, destroying it, and any Spiderlings on it.

returns.description: True if the cut was successfully started, false otherwise.

busy.description: When empty string this Spiderling is not busy, and can act. Otherwise a string representing what it is busy with, e.g. 'Moving', 'Attacking'.
